parameters: Search for yourself on social media

Memimi: For the management of the store, ego-searching is
very important... It allows us to hear the raw voices of our
customers and notice even the trivial things that I myself
might not be aware of.

Memimi: ...Of course, there are times when it's painful to
hear... but it's exactly those opinions that I must
gratefully review.

Memimi: Honestly, there are parts that are not good for my
mental health... frankly, I'm addicted to social media...
even with all that's written, I can't stop looking...

Memimi: Sigh... terrible photos have been uploaded to the
net... The fake news and reputational damage are severe...
There's no time to correct each one, and it would only add
fuel to the fire...

Memimi: They're writing such nonsense... I would never do
such things... But wearing perverted clothes and approaching
this person, or giving a blowjob, that's probably true...

Memimi: Why, why is this happening... Will I have to live
with the perception of being a promiscuous pervert from now
on...? I won't be able to show my face anywhere... uh, uh...

Memimi: Ah... Anomalocaris Mosman...? Someone is arguing
against the fake news...

Memimi: Surprisingly... there's a good side to Anomalocaris
Mosman after all... I feel a bit better now... hehe... thank
you...

"Who are you? Please don't say whatever you want from the
sidelines. Can you not make definitive statements without
evidence?"

"Don't be fooled! This person is a subordinate of Shark
Mountain Memimi! There's a possibility that insiders are
lying to put out the fire!"

"Annoying Anomalocaris Mosman! Read the room!! Your true
identity is the second son from the karate dojo in the
eastern district, right?! You've been exposed!"

Memimi: Ughhh, appearing on TV was definitely a bad idea...
It's blown up so much, there's not even a hint of it dying
down...

Memimi: Even the Gizagiza Mart account gets mountains of
comments every day, it's impossible to manage properly...
Why do they have to show images... even the other staff and
the big boss are seeing them...

Memimi: Gahhh, I can't take this anymore! It's depressing
right before a match... stop, just stop!

Memimi: At times like this, it's best to check out my hobby
account... The influencer Mr. British Gentleman introduces
stylish teas and such. He's a handsome gentleman and I'm a
big fan, secretly following him...

Memimi: Gone... No way... that's a lie... Mr. Gentleman
has... ah... why...

Cerberus Octopus: Shark Duke! This time, you're going to
take on the role of SNS public relations! Use the official
Gizagiza Mart account to promote the store!

Memimi: Hmph... acting all high and mighty... I've been
doing SNS promotion long before you told me to...

Cerberus Octopus: Hmm, I've been checking out your tweets
from time to time... but it's still not enough service!
Today, upload a selfie of your boobs!! It should change the
spread by an order of magnitude!

Memimi: You think everything can be solved with erotic
content, don't you...

Memimi: As if it wasn't bad enough that we're already in the
midst of a scandal, you want me to drop an erotic selfie...?
That guy is serious... ughh... doesn't he understand
anything about internet literacy... kuh...

Memimi: ...Upload... sighhh... I did it... ohh... I did
it... exposed my breasts to the whole world...

Memimi: Ahhh... it's spreading at an incredible rate...! No
way... it's already over 100 RTs... eek, 500... what, no
way, can't be true...!

Memimi: I'm not even a celebrity, but these numbers, I've
never seen anything like it before... It's going viral...
ahhh ahhh ahhh... how many tens of thousands have seen my
breasts now... sob... this is me...

Memimi: ...I did something bad at the last all-school
assembly, involving everyone because of my own issues...
That terrible first kiss was quite something too...

Memimi: As the student council president and at the top of
the school caste, naturally, I secretly know everyone's SNS
accounts too... I usually don't check them but... just a
little peek...

Memimi: What about Yamamoto-kun from class 2? His grades are
the second best after mine, he's cheerful, and we talk
sometimes... I even think he's kind of cool...

Memimi: Let's pretend I didn't see that... How about Inaba-
kun from the first year... Ever since I helped him when he
was lost in the school building after the entrance ceremony,
he's been so attached, calling me 'senpai, senpai'...

Memimi: I was foolish to expect even a little bit of
supportive words... I wonder if I can go back to being the
respected student council president like before if I defeat
Cerberus Octopus...? *sniffle*
